.TH man 1 "08 September 2022" "1.0"  "The simple_shell man page"

.SH NAME
.B hsh
- A basic UNIX command line interpreter.
.SH SYNOPSIS
 hsh can interpret and execute command line arguments read from the standard input.

.SH DESCRIPTION
The hsh shell is a program that reads line by line from a file or the terminal line. It then interprets the lines and executes it if the line is a valid command. 

.SH USAGE
All the files are to be compiled on an Ubuntu 20.04 LTS machine with "igcc -Wall -Werror -Wextra -pedantic -std=gnu89 *.c -o hsh".

Once compiled, to start the program, run:
.br
$ ./hsh

To exit the program, run:
.br
#cisfun$ exit

.SH BUILT-INS
The following built-ins are supported by the hsh shell:

.B env -
Print the current environment.

.B setenv VARIABLE VALUE - 
Initialize a new environment variable, or modify an existing one. 

.B unsetenv VARIABLE - 
Remove an environment variable.

.SH RETURN VALUE
hsh shell will exit with status 0 unless status is specified.

.SH SEE ALSO
.I sh(1)

.SH BUGS
No known bugs.

.SH AUTHOR
Endris Mohammed, Robel Adane